Collaborative Copyright and Revenue Sharing Framework for AI-Generated Works  
The copyright to any AI-generated musical composition that incorporates elements from copyrighted materials is jointly owned by three distinct parties: the user who prompted the creation, the company responsible for developing and operating the AI model (including its training data), and a representative body of original artists whose works contributed to the training dataset. In addition to joint ownership, a revenue sharing mechanism is mandated where profits derived from commercial exploitation (e.g., streaming, sales) are distributed as follows:  
– 40% allocated to the user for initiating the creative prompt;  
– 40% reserved for the company in recognition of its technological and infrastructural contributions;  
– 20% credited to the original artists, with distribution determined by an independent review board that assesses each artist's relative contribution.  
The framework also requires transparent documentation of all contributions and establishes a conflict resolution process overseen by a designated Creative Arbitration Panel composed of impartial experts in intellectual property law, music production, and AI technology.
